<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-77-0268 </DOCNO><TEXT>The development of new electronically conductive materials which can withstandthe environment of the positive plates has made possible the constructionof a high pulse power sealed bipolar lead-acid battery. The new batteryis described and its advantages over other electrochemical systems areoutlined. Performance projections show that the peak specific power ofthe battery can be as high as 90 kW/kg, and that a specific power of5 kW/kg can be sustained over several thousand pulses.</TEXT></DOC>